                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-184" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN EDWARDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Hutton and Co., of Newgate-street On 3d Nov. the prisoner came and asked for six yards of gimp, and pro<lb></lb>duced a pattern—it came to 9<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he tendered a bad crown-piece—I bent it, and took it to Mr. Hutton, who sent for a policeman, and the prisoner, was taken to the station—he said his mother, who lived on Bow-common, gave it him with the gimp.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you find his mother lived there. <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
