                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City policeman</hi>, 647). I received this crown from Mrs. Orpwood, and took the prisoner—he said, going to the station, "I expect Mr. Powell will prosecute, as I have been a day or two <hi rend="italic">in date</hi>"—I asked what he meant—he said, "They generally prosecute within fourteen days."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Is that the rule? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I cannot say—I did not mention Mr. Powell's name first.</p>
